What is the FCRA?
The Fair Credit Reporting Act ("FCRA") is a federal law that promotes the accuracy, fairness and privacy of information in the files of consumer reporting agencies.
Intelius does not provide consumer reports and is not a consumer reporting agency as defined by the FCRA. Intelius reports cannot be used for background checks related to consumer credit, insurance, employment, housing or any other purpose
                  prohibited under the FCRA.
You may not use any information obtained from Intelius for any purpose covered by the FCRA.
Find out more about the FCRA here.













Scott P. Scharfman: Executive Profile & Biography - Bloomberg









































  





















































































July 28, 2017 2:09 PM ET
Hotels, Restaurants and Leisure

Company Overview of MRRC Hold Co.



SnapshotPeopleÂ 




OverviewBoard MembersCommittees



Executive Profile
Scott P. Scharfman  President and Chief Executive Officer, MRRC Hold Co.AgeTotal Calculated CompensationThis person is connected to 3 Board Members in 3 different organizations across 4 different industries.See Board Relationships----
Background

		Mr. Scott P. Scharfman serves as a Managing Director at Mill Road Capital. Mr. Scharfman serves as the Chief Executive Officer and President at MRRC Hold Co. He also serves as an Advisor at i-Hatch Ventures LLC. Mr. Scharfman has over two decades of experience as an Investor, Investment Banker and Corporate Executive. Prior to joining Mill Road Capital, Mr. Scharfman served as the Senior Manager and Managing Director of the Equity Capital Markets Origination Group at ... Robertson Stephens. Prior to Robertson, he served as the Chief Financial Officer at Mercata, Inc. Prior to Mercata, Mr. Scharfman served as a Senior Managing Director and Head of the Equity Capital Markets Origination Group at Bear Stearns & Co. Prior to Bear Stearns, he served as a Senior Manager and Vice President at The Blackstone Group, investing Blackstone's funds in a variety of companies as well as advising clients on merger and acquisition strategy. Mr. Scharfman began his career in 1986 with The First Boston Corporation. He was on the team that took First Boston private in 1988. He is rChairman of the Board of PRT Growing Services Ltd. and R.G. Barry Corporation. Mr. Scharfman serves as a Member of the Board of Directors of Rubio's Restaurants, Inc. (former Chairman) and has served on Galaxy Nutritional Foods Inc. and MRRC Hold and multiple boards of both public and private companies. He has extensive experience trading equities as well as raising capital in initial public offerings, both equity and debt, secondaries and convertible offerings for companies in a wide variety of industries.  Mr. Scharfman holds an A.B. degree from Princeton University, where he graduated cum laude and was elected to Sigma Xi, the science honorary society.Read Full Background




